# select numeric variables
df_is.numeric <- df %>% 
  select_if(is.numeric)

df_heatmap <- round(cor(df_is.numeric, use = "complete.obs"), 1)
df_heatmap <- melt(df_heatmap)
## Warning in melt(df_heatmap): The melt generic in data.table has been passed a
## matrix and will attempt to redirect to the relevant reshape2 method; please note
## that reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well.
## To continue using melt methods from reshape2 while both libraries are attached,
## e.g. melt.list, you can prepend the namespace like reshape2::melt(df_heatmap).
## In the next version, this warning will become an error.
#  corrplot
ggplot(df_heatmap, aes(x=Var1, y=Var2, fill=value)) +
  geom_tile()+
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "pink", high = "dark red")+
  labs(title="Correlation Heatmap",x="", y="")+
  geom_text(aes(x=Var1, y=Var2, label=value), color="white")+
